h <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Maclean was born in Kingairloch, Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom as the daughter of Alexander Stewart. She married Lachlan Bronnach MacLean 7th. Chief of Clan MacLean before 1430. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1394–1463":"1394–1463","1416–1479":"1416–1479","–Male":"Surnud","1479":"1479","before 1430":"enne 1430","1463":"1463","1394":"1394","1416":"1416","Duart Castle, Isle of Mull, Scotland.":"Ardgour, Argyll, Scotland","Kingairloch, Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Kingairloch, Argyll, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1394–1463":"1394–1463","1416–1479":"1416–1479","–Male":"Kuollut","1479":"1479","before 1430":"ennen vuotta 1430","1463":"1463","1394":"1394","1416":"1416","Duart Castle, Isle of Mull, Scotland.":"Ardgour, Argyll, Scotland","Kingairloch, Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Kingairloch, Argyll, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","–Female":"Décédée","1394–1463":"1394–1463","1416–1479":"1416–1479","–Male":"Décédé","1479":"1479","before 1430":"avant 1430","1463":"1463","1394":"1394","1416":"1416","Duart Castle, Isle of Mull, Scotland.":"Ardgour, Argyll, Écosse","Kingairloch, Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Kingairloch, Argyll, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margaret Maclean est née à Kingairloch, Argyll, Écosse, Royaume-Uni, fille de Alexander Stewart. Elle a épousé Lachlan Bronnach MacLean 7th. Chief of Clan MacLean avant 1430. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1394–1463":"1394–1463","1416–1479":"1416–1479","–Male":"Verstorben","1479":"1479","before 1430":"vor 1430","1463":"1463","1394":"1394","1416":"1416","Duart Castle, Isle of Mull, Scotland.":"Ardgour, Argyll, Scotland","Kingairloch, Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Kingairloch, Argyll, Schottland, United Kingdom","lifeSumma